    • Method Detail

      • isValidWithComm

        protected boolean isValidWithComm(edu.jhu.hlt.concrete.Communication c)
        Description copied from class: AbstractAnnotation
        Implementors should implement this method, which will be called to attempt to validate the annotation object, via AbstractAnnotation.validate(Communication).

        As a result, you don't need to call AbstractAnnotation.isValid() on everything in your implementation of AbstractAnnotation.isValidWithComm(Communication).
        Specified by:
        isValidWithComm in class AbstractAnnotation<edu.jhu.hlt.concrete.EntityMention>
        Parameters:
        c - - A communication associated with the AbstractAnnotation.
        Returns:
        true if valid.
        See Also:
        AbstractAnnotation.validate(Communication)

      • isValid

        public boolean isValid()
        Description copied from class: AbstractAnnotation
        Annotations also have a notion of 'validity' on their own. For example, a UUID string may not be a correct UUID string, thus invalidating the individual annotation.
        Specified by:
        isValid in class AbstractAnnotation<edu.jhu.hlt.concrete.EntityMention>
        Returns:
        true if the individual annotation is valid.
